<body>

<div class="container">
    <h2>Ethical Challenges: Boundaries</h2>
    <p>A peer you are supporting asks if they can follow you on your personal Facebook account. As a Peer Worker, what is the most appropriate response?</p>

    <button class="choice-btn" onclick="checkAnswer(false, 'While tempting, this blurs professional boundaries. It is better to explain the agency policy on social media.')">A) Accept the request to build rapport.</button>
    
    <button class="choice-btn" onclick="checkAnswer(true, 'Correct! This maintains a safe space and follows the Code of Ethics regarding professional boundaries.')">B) Gently decline and explain the importance of maintaining a dedicated peer-support space.</button>
    
    <button class="choice-btn" onclick="checkAnswer(false, 'Simply ignoring the request can damage the relationship. A conversation about boundaries is necessary.')">C) Ignore the request and don\'t mention it.</button>

    <div id="result-box"></div>
</div>

<script>
    function checkAnswer(isCorrect, message) {
        const box = document.getElementById('result-box');
        box.style.display = 'block';
        box.innerHTML = message;
        box.className = isCorrect ? 'correct' : 'incorrect';
    }
</script>

</body>
